! Number-to-Letter Mapping
This system uses a custom letter mapping based on visual similarity or phonetic initials rather than the traditional Major System[cite: 1].

|!Digit |!Letter |!Logic |
|0 |O |Easy to remember (shape)[cite: 1] |
|1 |A |Alphabetical order[cite: 1] |
|2 |B |Alphabetical order[cite: 1] |
|3 |C |Alphabetical order[cite: 1] |
|4 |D |Alphabetical order[cite: 1] |
|5 |E |Alphabetical order[cite: 1] |
|6 |S |Visual similarity / "Six" starts with S[cite: 1] |
|7 |G |Alphabetical order[cite: 1] |
|8 |H |Alphabetical order[cite: 1] |
|9 |N |Easy to remember[cite: 1] |

